ons |\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` for Docker SDK integration (build, push, remove) |\n\n### 2.2 BuildRuntime Methods\n\n| Method | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `build(workspace_path, **options)` | Main orchestration entry point |\n| `_increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)` | Patch bump version (X.Y.Z ‚Üí X.Y.Z+1) or append .1 |\n| `_validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path)` | Check Docker availability, Dockerfile existence |\n| `_build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Local Docker build via SDK |\n| `_build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Cloud build (placeholder for future) |\n| `_update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, build_result, tag)` | Persist image info to metadata YAML |\n\n### 2.3 CLI Options\n\n| Option | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` / `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace directory |\n| `--proxy` / `-p` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution |\n| `--cloud-provider` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n| `--output` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path for build artifacts |\n| `--verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n\n### 2.4 Out of Scope\n\n| Item | Reason |\n|------|--------|\n| Cloud build implementation | Requires cloud provider SDK integration; placeholder only |\n| Multi-architecture builds | Not specified in requirements; future enhancement |\n| Build cache optimization | Docker SDK handles caching internally |\n| Image vulnerability scanning | Separate security concern |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis (ÂΩ±ÂìçÂàÜÊûê)\n\n### 3.1 Êñ∞Â¢ûÊñá‰ª∂\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ agentcube/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ runtime/\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ build_runtime.py      # BuildRuntime class\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ services/\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ docker_service.py     # DockerService class\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ cli/\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ main.py               # build command (addition to existing)\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ models/\n‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ pack_models.py        # MetadataOptions (shared with pack)\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ tests/\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ test_build_runtime.py     # Unit tests for BuildRuntime\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ test_docker_service.py    # Unit tests for DockerService\n```\n\n### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Impact |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python; required for local build |\n| `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n| `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and status output |\n| `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n| `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Version bump logic |\n\n### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Method Usage |\n|----------|--------------|\n| `publish` command | Uses built image name/tag from metadata |\n| `status` command | Reads image info from metadata |\n| `pack` command | Provides Dockerfile path for build |\n| Users | CLI invocation `kubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent` |\n\n### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **Metadata schema**: Adding `image` field with sub-fields (`image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`, `tag`) to `AgentMetadata`\n- **Version field**: Build modifies `metadata.version` in-place; concurrent builds could conflict\n- **Dockerfile location**: Build expects `Dockerfile` at workspace root (generated by `pack`)\n\n### 3.5 Compatibility Notes\n\n- Docker SDK `docker.from_env()` requires Docker daemon running\n- Version increment follows semver pattern: `X.Y.Z` ‚Üí `X.Y.(Z+1)`\n- Non-semver versions: append `.1` (e.g., `v1.0` ‚Üí `v1.0.1`)\n- Empty version: fallback to `{version}-1` or generate timestamp-based tag\n\n---\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered (Â§áÈÄâÊñπÊ°à)\n\n### Alternative 1: Shell Command Execution\n\n**Approach**: Execute `docker build` via `subprocess.run()` instead of Docker SDK.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Simpler implementation; no SDK dependency |\n| Cons | No structured output parsing; harder error handling; no image info extraction; platform-specific quirks |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Docker SDK provides structured image info (image_id, size) and cleaner exception handling.\n\n### Alternative 2: Kaniko for Rootless Builds\n\n**Approach**: Use Kaniko executor for builds without Docker daemon.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No Docker daemon required; CI-friendly; rootless |\n| Cons | Additional dependency; requires Kubernetes environment; not suitable for local dev workflow |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. May add as optional build backend for cloud mode.\n\n### Alternative 3: Buildah/Podman\n\n**Approach**: Support Buildah or Podman as alternative container build tools.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Daemonless; OCI-compliant; rootless option |\n| Cons | Different CLI interface; less Python SDK support; broader compatibility testing needed |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Docker SDK covers primary use case; Podman support could be future extension.\n\n### Alternative 4: Manual Version Management\n\n**Approach**: Require user to specify version via `--version` flag instead of auto-increment.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Explicit control; no rollback complexity |\n| Cons | Manual burden; potential duplicate tags; workflow friction |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Auto-increment with rollback on failure provides safer workflow per spec requirements.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Docker daemon unavailable | `_validate_build_prerequisites` checks `DockerService.check_docker_available()` before build |\n| Version rollback race condition | Build modifies metadata file; use atomic write pattern |\n| Build timeout on large images | Docker SDK streaming build; no explicit timeout in spec |\n| Registry auth for push (future) | `DockerService._docker_login_sdk` handles auth when credentials provided |\n| Image name collision | Use `{agent_name}:{version}` pattern; sanitize agent_name |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Implement `DockerService.check_docker_available()` with `docker.from_env()` try/catch\n- [ ] Implement `DockerService.build_image()` with streaming logs, build_args for proxy\n- [ ] Implement `DockerService.get_image_info()` for image_id, size extraction\n- [ ] Implement `DockerService.push_image()` with optional registry auth\n- [ ] Implement `DockerService.remove_image()` with graceful failure handling\n- [ ] Implement `BuildRuntime._increment_version()` with semver logic\n- [ ] Implement `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()` for Docker + Dockerfile check\n- [ ] Implement `BuildRuntime._build_local()` orchestrating Docker build\n- [ ] Implement `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata()` persisting results\n- [ ] Add `build` Typer command in `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n- [ ] Add error handling with `_handle_error()` for verbose traceback\n- [ ] Add Rich `Progress` spinner for build status\n- [ ] Add `image` field to `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n- [ ] Unit tests for version increment edge cases\n- [ ] Unit tests for Docker unavailable scenarios\n- [ ] Integration test for full build workflow\n\n---\n\n## 7. References\n\n- Spec: `changes/AR-021/spec.md`\n- Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n- CLI Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` ‚Äî Requirement: `build` command\n- Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n- Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n- Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/","additions":135,"deletions":15},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775869914470,"end":1775869914507}}}}
